official-title.#text: Commemorating the 150th anniversary of Mayo Clinic.

committee-name.#text: Committee on Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions

cosponsor.#tail: ) submitted the following resolution; which was referred to the

action-desc.#text: Committee discharged; considered and agreed to

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: commemorates the 150th anniversary of Mayo Clinic.

text.#text:
Whereas Dr. William Worrall Mayo first announced his plans to establish a medical practice in
			 Rochester, Minnesota, on January 27, 1864;
Whereas 2014 marks 150 years of Mayo Clinic providing continuous, quality service to patients;

Whereas the Mayo Clinic model of integrated, high-quality health care has become an international
			 model for providing health care;
Whereas the many historic achievements of Mayo Clinic include—
developing the first integrated, multi-specialty practice of medicine;
creating the first anti-blackout suits for military pilots during World War II;
winning the Nobel Prize in 1950 for discovering cortisone;
developing a DNA test that detects anthrax in less than 1 hour; and

continuing a tradition of helping individuals in the most need of help, including by deploying
			 medical teams to earthquake-stricken Haiti;

Whereas Mayo Clinic continues to value compassion, integrity, quality, and innovation in its
			 leadership around the world; and

Whereas Mayo Clinic is considered a premiere global center of health and healing dedicated to
			 medical care, research, and education: Now, therefore, be it

{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}title.#text: 113 SRES 339 ATS: Commemorating the 150th anniversary of Mayo Clinic.
